    "This is why Arnold and Slack's diamond con worked — not because of fake gems or bribed experts, but because two country rubes in ill-fitting pants were simply unimaginable as the architects of the century's biggest financial fraud. The financiers, generals, and jewelers all had the same thought: men this naive cannot possibly be deceiving us. That thought was the con.",
