    "The ancient Chinese called it 'masquerading as a swine to kill the tiger.' The tiger lets the pig get close because it sees only an easy meal. The hunter wearing the pig's hide has the last laugh. Arrogant people are especially vulnerable to this — the easier they believe you are to defeat, the more completely off-guard you can catch them.",
    "This tactic is not just for cons and negotiations. Claudius and the young Louis XIII both played the fool as young men while others around them competed dangerously for power. They were left alone, even promoted, because no one feared them. When the moment to act came, they struck with a decisiveness that shocked everyone — precisely because no one had been watching.",
